Installation on Linux/Unix
----------------------------

[Requirements]:
GNU make (For installation)
Perl
 
[Install]:
You have to be root for the installation.
Execute to install the scripts and manpage:
# make install

Now subcheck.pl and all-checksub and installed in /usr/bin


Installation on MS Windows:
---------------------------
[Requirements]:
Perl (get it at http://www.activeperl.com/)
 
[Install]:
There is no actual installation for MS Windows.
The only thing you have to do is to open a command-line
such as "command.com". Now go to the directory where subcheck.pl
is located. And run it just like a normal executable.
